@Jessica 
Claure Rebussy is one of my favorite composers!
(I especially love his tone poem, *La Med.")

@Andrzej 

Camel rides sound pretty cool.  I was on the back of an elephant with my son at a zoo when he was young.

Yes, let's meet.  Half way?  Approximately the Sargasso Sea, perhaps?

@Andrzej 

I was trying to come up with another joke, and couldn't.  And then you come up with seahorses!

I'd be jealous if I wasn't so amused.

@HeathieJ

Thanks for the tip!  I ran into the same problem.  I followed your advice:  got rid of all the rebusses and just typed U where the rebusses were to go. 
Got the happy music and  my streak continues …

@HeathieJ 

While I do think rebus puzzles are fair game, I do think there it makes it difficult to evaluate for correctness.  For example, U/KEY might work (it seems it does), but U KEY or U,KEY, or U-KEY doesn't.  

I don't think I've ever seen a rebus that didn't have someone claiming to have entered it right and didn't get the music.  I believe them, and it must be quite annoying.
